"n. 懦夫，胆小的人 无 n. 懦夫; 胆小的人 【记】读: 打死他的－这种人得打死他, 见死不救, 是个懦夫 【类】dastard: craven 懦夫: 懦夫 无 dastard (n.)  mid-15c., ""one who is lazy or dull;"" an English formation on a French model, probably from *dast, ""dazed,"" past participle of dasen ""to daze"" (see daze (v.)) + deprecatory suffix -ard. Meaning ""one who shirks from danger"" is late 15c."
